        <!-- WebGazer Instructions -->
        <div class="info" id="webgazerInstructions">
            <h1>WebGazer Eye Tracking Calibration</h1>
            <h2>Please allow webcam access before starting the calibration.</h2>

            <p>1. Intial view. </p>
            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <img src="/public/assets/eyetrackinginstructions1.png"  class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">

            <p>2. Focus and begin left mouse clicking on one blue square. </p>
            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <img src="/public/assets/eyetrackinginstructions2.png"  class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">

            <p>3. The square will turn red when calibrated </p>
            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <img src="/public/assets/eyetrackinginstructions3.png"  class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 400px; height: auto;">

            <p>Look at the screen with blue squares as shown in the first image.</p>
            <p>Focus on one blue square at a time.</p>
            <p>While looking at the square, click on it 5 times.</p>
            <p>Keep your gaze on the square until it turns red.</p>
            <p>Move to the next blue square and repeat steps 2-4.</p>
            <p>Continue until all squares have turned red.</p>
            <p class="important-note">For optimal eye tracking performance, maintain your focus on only the square you are clicking on throughout the process.</p>
            <button type="button" id="continue">Continue</button>
        </div>
    
    </body>
    <script>
        document.getElementById("continue").addEventListener("click", () => {
            window.location.href = '/information/webgazerconfig';
